059/**
060 * An <strong>experimental</strong> {@link TypeElement} implementation that is wholly synthetic and suitable only for
061 * (partially) modeling {@linkplain AnnotationMirror#getAnnotationType() annotation types}.
062 *
063 * @author <a href="https://about.me/lairdnelson" target="_top">Laird Nelson</a>
064 *
065 * @see SyntheticAnnotationMirror
066 */
067public final class SyntheticAnnotationTypeElement implements TypeElement {
068
069  private static final Set<Modifier> modifiers = Set.of(ABSTRACT);
070
071  private final List<? extends AnnotationMirror> annotationMirrors;
072
073  private final SyntheticName fqn;
074
075  private final Type type;
076
077  private final List<? extends InternalAnnotationElement> elements;
078
079  /**
080   * Creates a new {@link SyntheticAnnotationTypeElement}.
081   *
082   * @param annotationMirrors a {@link List} of {@link AnnotationMirror}s modeling the annotations this element has;
083   * must not be {@code null}
084   *
085   * @param fullyQualifiedName the fully qualified name of the synthetic element; must conform to Java classname
086   * restrictions; must not be {@code null}
087   *
088   * @param elements a {@link List} of {@link SyntheticAnnotationElement}s modeling the annotation elements; must not be
089   * {@code null}
090   *
091   * @exception NullPointerException if any argument is {@code null}
092   *
093   * @exception IllegalArgumentException if {@code fullyQualifiedName} does not conform to Java classname restrictions
094   *
095   * @see SyntheticAnnotationElement
096   *
097   * @see SyntheticAnnotationMirror
098   */
099  public SyntheticAnnotationTypeElement(final List<? extends AnnotationMirror> annotationMirrors,
100                                        final String fullyQualifiedName,
101                                        final List<? extends SyntheticAnnotationElement> elements) {
102    super();
103    this.annotationMirrors = List.copyOf(annotationMirrors);
104    this.fqn = SyntheticName.of(fullyQualifiedName);
105    this.type = new Type();
106    final List<InternalAnnotationElement> elements0 = new ArrayList<>(elements.size());
107    for (final SyntheticAnnotationElement e : elements) {
108      elements0.add(new InternalAnnotationElement(e.annotationMirrors(), e.type(), e.name()));
109    }
110    this.elements = unmodifiableList(elements0);
111  }
112
113  @Override // Element
114  public final <R, P> R accept(final ElementVisitor<R, P> v, final P p) {
115    return v.visitType(this, p);
116  }
117

120    return this.type;
121  }

126  }

131  }

136  }

141  }

173  @Override
174  public final Name getSimpleName() {
175    final String fqn = this.getQualifiedName().toString();
176    final int i = fqn.lastIndexOf('.');
177    return i >= 0 ? SyntheticName.of(fqn.substring(i + 1)) : this.getQualifiedName();
178  }

195  /**
196   * An <strong>experimental</strong> collection of information out of which a synthetic annotation element may be
197   * fashioned.
198   *
199   * @author <a href="https://about.me/lairdnelson" target="_top">Laird Nelson</a>
200   */
201  public static final class SyntheticAnnotationElement {
202
203    private final List<? extends AnnotationMirror> annotationMirrors;
204
205    private final TypeMirror type;
206
207    private final String name;
208
209    /**
210     * Creates a new {@link SyntheticAnnotationElement}.
211     *
212     * @param annotationMirrors a {@link List} of {@link AnnotationMirror}s modeling the annotations this element has;
213     * must not be {@code null}
214     *
215     * @param type the type of the annotation element; must conform to Java annotation element type restrictions; must
216     * not be {@code null}
217     *
218     * @param name the name of the annotation element; must conform to Java method naming requirements; must not be
219     * {@code null}
220     *
221     * @exception NullPointerException if any argument is {@code null}
222     *
223     * @exception IllegalArgumentException if any argument does not conform to its requirements
224     */
225    public SyntheticAnnotationElement(final List<? extends AnnotationMirror> annotationMirrors,
226                                      final TypeMirror type, // the "return type"
227                                      final String name) {
228      super();
229      this.annotationMirrors = List.copyOf(annotationMirrors);
230      this.type = requireNonNull(type, "type");
231      this.name = requireNonNull(name, "name");
232    }
233
234    final List<? extends AnnotationMirror> annotationMirrors() {
235      return this.annotationMirrors;
236    }
237
238    @Override // Object
239    public final boolean equals(final Object other) {
240      return this == other || switch (other) {
241      case null -> false;
242      case SyntheticAnnotationElement sae when this.getClass() == sae.getClass() ->
243      Objects.equals(this.name, sae.name) &&
244      Objects.equals(this.type, sae.type) &&
245      Objects.equals(this.annotationMirrors, sae.annotationMirrors);
246      default -> false;
247      };
248    }
249
250    @Override // Object
251    public final int hashCode() {
252      int hashCode = 31;
253      int c = this.name.hashCode();
254      hashCode = 17 * hashCode + c;
255      c = this.type.hashCode();
256      hashCode = 17 * hashCode + c;
257      c = this.annotationMirrors.hashCode();
258      hashCode = 17 * hashCode + c;
259      return hashCode;
260    }
261
262    final String name() {
263      return this.name;
264    }
265
266    final TypeMirror type() {
267      return this.type;
268    }
269
270  }

443    private static final class Type implements ExecutableType {
444
445      private final TypeMirror type;
446
447      private Type(final TypeMirror type) {
448        super();
449        this.type = validate(type);
450      }
451
452      private static TypeMirror validate(final TypeMirror type) {
453        TypeMirror t = type;
454        TypeKind k = t.getKind();
455        if (k == ARRAY && t instanceof ArrayType a) {
456          t = a.getComponentType();
457          k = t.getKind();
458        }
459        if (k.isPrimitive()) {
460          return type;
461        }
462        if (k == DECLARED) {
463          final TypeElement e = (TypeElement)((DeclaredType)t).asElement();
464          switch (e.getKind()) {
465          case ANNOTATION_TYPE:
466          case ENUM:
467            return type;
468          case CLASS:
469            final Name fqn = e.getQualifiedName();
470            if (fqn.contentEquals("java.lang.String") || fqn.contentEquals("java.lang.Class")) {
471              return type;
472            }
473            break;
474          default:
475            break;
476          }
477        }
478        throw new IllegalArgumentException("type: " + type);
479      }
480
481      @Override // TypeMirror
482      public final <R, P> R accept(final TypeVisitor<R, P> v, final P p) {
483        return v.visitExecutable(this, p);
484      }
485
486      @Override // ExecutableType (AnnotatedConstruct)
487      public final <A extends Annotation> A getAnnotation(final Class<A> annotationType) {
488        throw new UnsupportedOperationException(); // deliberate
489      }
490
491      @Override // ExecutableType (AnnotatedConstruct)
492      public final List<? extends AnnotationMirror> getAnnotationMirrors() {
493        return List.of(); // can't actually put type annotations on an executable type to my knowledge
494      }
495
496      @Override // ExecutableType (AnnotatedConstruct)
497      public final <A extends Annotation> A[] getAnnotationsByType(final Class<A> annotationType) {
498        throw new UnsupportedOperationException(); // deliberate
499      }
500
501      @Override // ExecutableType (TypeMirror)
502      public final TypeKind getKind() {
503        return TypeKind.EXECUTABLE;
504      }
505
506      @Override // ExecutableType
507      public final List<? extends TypeMirror> getParameterTypes() {
508        return List.of();
509      }
510
511      @Override // ExecutableType
512      public final TypeMirror getReceiverType() {
513        return NoneType.of();
514      }
515
516      @Override // ExecutableType
517      public final TypeMirror getReturnType() {
518        return this.type;
519      }
520
521      @Override // ExecutableType
522      public final List<? extends TypeMirror> getThrownTypes() {
523        return List.of();
524      }
525
526      @Override // ExecutableType
527      public final List<? extends TypeVariable> getTypeVariables() {
528        return List.of();
529      }
530
531    }
